name: instrument-server
description: Instrument Server is a framework for creating Test & Measurement (T&M) application microservices.

name: QuickpollApplication
description: From Book Spring REST Building Microservices and Cloud Applications by B.Varanasi and M.Bartkov

name: TouristGuide-MicroservicesWebApp
description: Web application that connects guides and tourists developed with microservice architecture using API-REST between microservices and API-GATEWAY which connects through Graphql requests with the developed graphical user interface.

name: Refactor-Monolith-to-Microservices
description: Now that we have learned about monolith applications and microservices, let's do it ourselves! For our project, we will be taking an existing monolith application and deploy it as microservices in Kubernetes on AWS.  Refactor the monolith application to microservices Set up each microservice to be run in its own Docker container Set up a CI/CD pipeline to deploy the containers to Kubernetes

name: Curreny-Microservice-V2
description: A web application that follows micro service architecture and is used to convert currency values. It involves two microservices, i.e a currency exchange microservice and a currency conversion microservice created with the help of Spring boot and Spring cloud and mongodb is used as the database to store the currency exchange values.

name: veterinaryexample
description: The VeterinaryExample is an application using SAO architecture. implemented differentes microservices with SpringBoot and RabbitMq like message middleware. Using the microservices desing patter SAGA.

name: polo-nodejs
description: Polo API is a lightweight messenger API for asynchronous message exchange between applications in a microservice environment.

name: Identidock
description: A simple application that provides  users with identicons based on hashing a submitted username. I employed a microservice approach where the python web application talks to a JavaScript service and a C key-value store (redis) across three containers.

name: Fields_Report
description: REST API with a purpose of collecting daily production rates of oil and gas fields. The application is designed as a microservice working together with a Field Library REST API

name: INFOMSWA
description: This repo hosts the microservice application demo that was build using Java Spring Boot for Utrecht University's course Software Architecture '21/'22. It is a payment system for public transport that is secure, fast, and scalable.
